An ArrayList is a data structure used to store elemens, and it can increase or decrease the size dinamically.

To use this data structure in Java we have to import it.

import java.util.ArrayList;

ArrayList<Type> arrayList = new ArrayList<>()

3.1 Adding a new element

arrayList.add()

3.2 Deleting an element

arrayList.remove(element)
arrayList.remove(index)

3.3 Size of array

arrayList.size()